  <h1 id="header">Welcome to My Webpage</h1>
  <p>This narrative, "The Lost Key," sets a scene common to many family histories</p>
  <p class="intro">sets a scene common to many family histories: the discovery of an old object that connects a new generation to the past. The opening lines, "Every family has a story, a treasured object that holds more history than meets the eye," function as both a philosophical statement and a narrative hook, inviting the reader to consider their own family's relics.</p>
  <p class="highlight"> By immediately introducing a tangible mystery a key hidden under a floorboard the story creates an intimate atmosphere and a sense of intrigue. The discovery by a curious child serves as the inciting incident, symbolizing the moment the past and present collide</p>
  <div class="box">
    <p>An old, rusty key found under a floorboard connects a child to their family's past, turning a forgotten object into a treasured heirloom. The key, which has an unknown purpose, becomes a symbol of the family's shared history and the mysteries it holds. The story is not about what the key unlocks physically, but about the emotional and historical significance it unlocks for the family. </p>
  </div>
